{
  "local_port": 40728,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are some interesting fiction books available?",
  "response": "Here are some interesting fiction books from various genres that you might enjoy:\n\n1. **\"The Midnight Library\" by Matt Haig**\n   - Genre: Fantasy, Literary Fiction\n   - Synopsis: Nora Seed finds herself in a library between life and death, where she can live out alternate versions of her life by choosing different books. It's a touching exploration of regret, choices, and the possibilities of life.\n\n2. **\"Project Hail Mary\" by Andy Weir**\n   - Genre: Science Fiction\n   - Synopsis: Ryland Grace wakes up from a coma on a spaceship with no memory of who he is or why he's there. As he pieces together his mission, he must find a way to save humanity from an impending disaster. Fans of \"The Martian\" will love this thrilling adventure.\n\n3. **\"Circe\" by Madeline Miller**\n   - Genre: Historical Fiction, Mythology\n   - Synopsis: This novel reimagines the story of Circe, a minor goddess in Greek mythology, as she navigates her powers and her place in the world. It's a beautifully written tale of self-discovery and defiance.\n\n4. **\"The Seven Husbands of Evelyn Hugo\" by Taylor Jenkins Reid**\n   - Genre: Historical Fiction, Romance\n   - Synopsis: Aging Hollywood star Evelyn Hugo recounts her life and seven marriages to an unknown journalist. This captivating story delves into the glamour and scandal of old Hollywood, with themes of love, ambition, and identity.\n\n5. **\"The Night Circus\" by Erin Morgenstern**\n   - Genre: Fantasy, Romance\n   - Synopsis: A magical circus that only appears at night serves as the backdrop for a competition between two young illusionists who fall in love. The enchanting atmosphere and intricate plot make this a must-read.\n\n6. **\"Where the Crawdads Sing\" by Delia Owens**\n   - Genre: Literary Fiction, Mystery\n   - Synopsis: Kya, known as the \"Marsh Girl,\" grows up isolated in the marshes of North Carolina. When a popular young man is found dead, she becomes a suspect. This novel weaves a tale of nature, survival, and the complexities of human relationships.\n\n7. **\"The Invisible Life of Addie LaRue\" by V.E. Schwab**\n   - Genre: Fantasy, Historical Fiction\n   - Synopsis: In 1714 France, Addie LaRue makes a Faustian bargain to live forever but be forgotten by everyone she meets. Spanning centuries, this book explores themes of memory, art, and the desire to leave a mark on the world.\n\nThese books span a range of genres and themes, so there should be something to pique your interest no matter what type of fiction you enjoy. Happy reading!",
